						| ransition
						br
						br
						a(href="/images/ATP-sponsorship-packet.pdf" target='_blank').btn.btn-lg.btn-primary Become a sponsor
	//- About Us Section
	#team
		.container
			.row
				.col-xs-12
					h3.text-center Meet the team behind the talk
					//- p.heading__sub	
			.row
				.col-md-10.col-md-offset-1
					.row
						.col-lg-3.col-sm-6.col-xs-8.col-xs-offset-2.col-sm-offset-0
							.team__item
								a#jmbutton(role='button' data-toggle='collapse' href='#jmbio' aria-expanded="false" aria-controls='collapseExample')
									.team-item__img
										img.btn-block.img-responsive(src='images/JM Individual.jpg', alt='Photo of Jasper Matthews')
								.row
									.col-xs-6
										.team-item__name Jasper Matthews M.Ed.
										.team-item__position Host/Executive Producer
									.col-xs-6
										.team-item__contact
											a.team-item-contact__link(href='mailto:jmatthews@thegreatacademy.org')
												i.fa.fa-envelope-o
											.clearfix
						.col-lg-9.col-sm-6.col-xs-8.col-xs-offset-2.col-sm-offset-0
							#jmbio.collapse
								.well
									h2 Jasper Matthews M.Ed. - Host/Executive Producer
									p 
									| Jasper obtained a BA in both Sociology and African American Studies from the University of New Mexico in 1998. He received an MA in K-12 Special Education from the College of Santa Fe - Albuquerque in 2002. His program and Master's Thesis centered on charter administration and management. He is currently a PhD candidate in Educational Leadership at Capella University. His research focus is Response to Intervention (RtI), school reform and closing the achievement gap. During his six years of administrative experience, he served as the Assistant Principal of Valencia High School, Assistant Principal of Horizon Academy Northwest Charter School, Assistant Principal at Armijo Elementary School and served as the Dean of Students at Horizon Academy South. Jasper has been in education a total of 18 years and has served as an Educational Assistant, Special Education Teacher, Dean of Students, Assistant Principal and Director/Principal. In addition, Jasper is the Founder/Executive Director of The GREAT Academy – Albuquerque, which is in its fifth successful year.
